On 10/26/04 8:04 AM, "J Barry Burneskis" <honey_bus(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> Hey, I am happy to see 13.2 volts at my special dash board connection
> (silver socket) when I am driving my '78 USA federal non-air conditioning
> type 2.
>
> But people (Bentley) seem to think I should be getting 14 volts.

If your lights are on that's normal. If not, it's a little low. Remember,
the flow of current from the battery down the umbilical wire to the dash
will cause a voltage drop proportional to the resitance of the wire.
 
> Could it be that my regualtor is regulating my voltage to just over 13
> volts, and if I get a different regulator I would see the 'desired' 14
> volts??

Maybe. What's your voltage reading at the battery?

